summary: This is an email chain from October 2020 between US Attorney's Office personnel (likely Southern District of New York) and NYPD, following up on a request for an FBI 302 form (interview report) for a witness. The email indicates an ongoing investigation or case review requiring witness documentation.
keyFacts: Email communication dated October 23, 2020, between the US Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York (USANYS) and the NYPD.
The US Attorney's Office is requesting an FBI 302 form (witness interview report) from the NYPD.
The email indicates an ongoing investigative or prosecutorial effort requiring witness documentation, potentially related to the Epstein case.
The correspondence shows coordination between federal prosecutors and local law enforcement regarding witness information.
